WEBVTT

00:07.572 --> 00:10.140
- Look at her.
Teeth capped, I'm sure.

00:10.184 --> 00:12.316
You know, she's got the money.
She can afford to be that much

00:12.360 --> 00:14.144
prettier than me.
- Oh, my God, please.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.841
That bitch is
all about the filters.

00:15.885 --> 00:19.236
There's no way
she's prettier than you.

00:19.280 --> 00:20.803
I promise.

00:22.848 --> 00:24.937
I promise.

00:24.981 --> 00:29.725
- You know, if you're lying,
I'll have to kill you.

00:29.768 --> 00:32.728
[Cat Clyde's "So Heavy"
playing]

00:32.771 --> 00:34.773
♪

00:34.817 --> 00:36.427
[both laugh softly]

00:36.471 --> 00:39.300
- ♪ Just to watch it bleed

00:39.343 --> 00:41.998
♪ And it's so heavy

00:42.042 --> 00:46.872
♪ Too heavy to hold

00:46.916 --> 00:50.093
♪

00:50.137 --> 00:54.315
♪ I wash my cup

00:54.358 --> 00:57.361
♪ Love with doubt

01:02.497 --> 01:04.281
- [breathes deeply]

01:04.325 --> 01:07.241
- Ready?

01:07.284 --> 01:09.417
You know what they'd
call you back in Sinaloa?

01:09.460 --> 01:10.418
- Huh?

01:10.461 --> 01:11.810
- Sicario de nacimiento.

01:11.854 --> 01:14.161
- [laughs softly]
- Sicario.

01:14.204 --> 01:16.163
- Mm-hmm.
- Like my boy Benicio.

01:16.206 --> 01:18.469
- [laughs]
- What's the rest mean?

01:18.513 --> 01:20.819
- Natural born, baby.

01:22.430 --> 01:24.823
Natural born.

01:24.867 --> 01:27.826
[tense music]

01:27.870 --> 01:31.917
♪

01:31.961 --> 01:35.791
- How about some bougie tacos?

01:35.834 --> 01:39.273
Remember that place
by the PetSmart?

01:39.316 --> 01:42.232
Oaxaca Flats.
- Love it, see you then.

01:42.276 --> 01:44.104
- Can't wait.

01:50.806 --> 01:52.199
Jared?

01:52.242 --> 01:55.550
[gasps, grunts]

01:59.162 --> 02:02.687
[groaning]

02:04.602 --> 02:06.735
- What the hell?

02:17.224 --> 02:18.703
- [gasps]

02:23.012 --> 02:25.145
- Who's prettier now?

02:27.103 --> 02:28.539
[breathes heavily]

02:28.583 --> 02:30.846
- [grunting]

02:38.070 --> 02:41.944
- And the hawk wasn't moving.

02:41.987 --> 02:44.947
It was just lying there,
and then stupid Ross

02:44.990 --> 02:47.167
picked up a stick and poked it.

02:47.210 --> 02:52.346
I tried to stop him,
but all the boys just laughed.

02:52.389 --> 02:55.087
And then Ross killed it.

02:55.131 --> 02:58.743
- That's terrible, sweetheart.So cruel.

03:00.658 --> 03:02.094
Do you want meto call their parents?

03:02.138 --> 03:04.967
- No.

03:05.010 --> 03:08.362
- I made you some
hot chocolate, sweetie.

03:08.405 --> 03:09.754
- Somebody needs to talkto this boy.

03:09.798 --> 03:13.062
His behavioris really disturbing.

03:13.105 --> 03:14.542
Maybe I should call the school.

03:14.585 --> 03:17.675
- I don't know.
- [sighs]

03:19.634 --> 03:21.549
I have to go.But I promise,

03:21.592 --> 03:24.116
soon as I get back,we'll take care of this.

03:24.160 --> 03:26.423
I'll think of what to do.
I love you, sweetheart.

03:26.467 --> 03:27.729
- Love you too.

03:27.772 --> 03:29.861
[spoon clinks]

03:29.905 --> 03:31.994
[sighs]

03:32.037 --> 03:34.518
- Connie Romano, 28,
nursing student.

03:34.562 --> 03:37.260
Just before hightailing out
of the High Point Apartment

03:37.304 --> 03:39.088
parking garage in Hamilton,
New Jersey.

03:39.131 --> 03:42.265
Presumably in that
2012 Hyundai.

03:42.309 --> 03:45.442
Dr. Melissa Alden, 30,
pediatric shrink.

03:45.486 --> 03:49.054
Found with a single 9mm bullet
lodged in her skull.

03:49.098 --> 03:51.013
Sadly for her,
it wasn't a kill shot.

03:51.056 --> 03:53.668
She survived the bullet,
only to be stomped to death.

03:53.711 --> 03:55.278
- Witnesses?

03:55.322 --> 03:57.062
- Just one functional
security camera.

03:57.106 --> 03:59.674
Caught an unidentified white
male with a neck tattoo

03:59.717 --> 04:02.851
exiting a vehicle, carrying
a gun, silencer attached.

04:02.894 --> 04:05.549
A second unidentified party,
likely female,

04:05.593 --> 04:07.856
behind the wheel.
- Stomped to death?

04:07.899 --> 04:10.032
Something personal.
- Local cops talked

04:10.075 --> 04:12.600
to Dr. Alden's fiancé,
a plastic surgeon.

04:12.643 --> 04:14.428
Connie Romano
is his ex-girlfriend

04:14.471 --> 04:16.908
as of six months ago.
- I'm guessing Connie wasn't

04:16.952 --> 04:18.693
happy about his
engagement to Melissa.

04:18.736 --> 04:20.912
- Connie was totally
obsessed with Melissa.

04:20.956 --> 04:23.175
Her cloud account's busting
with photos of Melissa

04:23.219 --> 04:25.395
she hacked
from the ex-fiancé's Facebook.

04:25.439 --> 04:28.093
She paired them up with photos
of her own with the fiancé

04:28.137 --> 04:30.792
from happier times.

04:30.835 --> 04:34.143
[suspenseful music]

04:34.186 --> 04:36.885
♪

04:36.928 --> 04:38.930
- Guess the guy has a type.

04:38.974 --> 04:40.845
both: Melissa's prettier.

04:40.889 --> 04:43.326
- They said it first.

04:43.370 --> 04:46.155
- Dumped for a more attractive,
more successful version

04:46.198 --> 04:48.288
of yourself?
Man, that's rough.

04:48.331 --> 04:50.812
- Luckily, most of us
get over it.

04:50.855 --> 04:52.944
- CID have any evidence
that Connie's fleeing

04:52.988 --> 04:55.773
the jurisdiction?
- She has a Sinaloa Cartel

04:55.817 --> 04:58.385
connection through
her cousin, Ernesto Cruz.

04:58.428 --> 05:00.996
When she was 16, Connie
and Cruz were caught in Texas

05:01.039 --> 05:03.346
with 57 handguns in their car.

05:03.390 --> 05:05.609
Cruz did eight years
for gunrunning,

05:05.653 --> 05:08.308
Connie got probation.
- So we're worried she might

05:08.351 --> 05:10.527
run to her Cartel friends
across the border.

05:10.571 --> 05:11.963
- That's where I'd go.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.357
- Any excuse to get
a good mole.

05:14.401 --> 05:17.969
- Get a beat on cousin Ernesto,
put an agent on him.

05:18.013 --> 05:19.710
- It was all falling
into place.

05:19.754 --> 05:23.801
I had, uh, just got an offer
from a practice in Oahu.

05:23.845 --> 05:25.977
Um, Melissa had scored
a job there.

05:26.021 --> 05:28.371
We were gonna get
married on the beach.

05:28.415 --> 05:30.242
And we were weeks away.
[sighs]

05:30.286 --> 05:32.462
I'm sorry, it's just--

05:32.506 --> 05:34.290
she was so kind, she was the...

05:34.334 --> 05:36.945
- We're very sorry, Dr. Pierce.
- Never, in a million years,

05:36.988 --> 05:40.165
did I think Connie was
capable of something like this.

05:40.209 --> 05:43.430
I mean, our--our breakup,
it was--it was amicable.

05:43.473 --> 05:45.693
- Amicable means nothingto somebody like Connie.

05:45.736 --> 05:47.869
Have you spoken to hersince you broke up?

05:47.912 --> 05:50.219
- No, not since, um,
she moved out.

05:50.262 --> 05:52.917
- Now, you told the police thatyou didn't recognize any of her

05:52.961 --> 05:54.789
accomplicesin the surveillance photos.

05:54.832 --> 05:56.138
- Well, you couldn't
see very much.

05:56.181 --> 05:58.140
- You dated her for two years.

06:01.361 --> 06:04.320
- She never mentioned having a
connection to a Mexican cartel?

06:04.364 --> 06:08.150
- No, she's not even Mexican.

06:08.193 --> 06:09.760
[sighs]
This is a nightmare.

06:09.804 --> 06:11.893
Look, am--am I in danger?

06:11.936 --> 06:14.765
- We'll post agents here
and outside your home.

06:14.809 --> 06:17.986
[foreboding music]

06:18.029 --> 06:20.728
- You know, Connie might
have been stalking you

06:20.771 --> 06:24.296
without you being aware.
Do you remember any incidents

06:24.340 --> 06:26.560
or strangers coming
to your office?

06:26.603 --> 06:28.736
♪

06:28.779 --> 06:31.129
- Maybe.
Uh, a couple weeks ago,

06:31.173 --> 06:32.827
right after we posted
our engagement.

06:32.870 --> 06:35.090
I was at the coffee shop
across the street from here,

06:35.133 --> 06:37.788
and this woman came up to me.
She was in a uniform.

06:37.832 --> 06:40.661
A security guard.
And she said that she worked

06:40.704 --> 06:42.576
in Melissa's building,
and that I had the right

06:42.619 --> 06:46.928
to know that Melissa
entertained other men.

06:46.971 --> 06:50.845
- Can you describe her?
- Like, a hat, sunglasses,

06:50.888 --> 06:53.587
I think she was Latin,
not too tall.

06:53.630 --> 06:54.979
I didn't think much of it.

06:55.023 --> 06:56.372
Look, maybe if I had taken it

06:56.416 --> 07:00.332
a little more seriously, I--
I could've--

07:00.376 --> 07:04.206
I don't know, I...

07:04.249 --> 07:06.861
- Looks like a hurricane
hit this place.

07:06.904 --> 07:11.300
Keep hope alive.
Denial meets delusion.

07:11.343 --> 07:13.781
- Connie wouldn't see
anything to deny or delude

07:13.824 --> 07:16.131
herself about.
To a psychopath, only their

07:16.174 --> 07:18.742
feelings matter.
Whatever the other person might

07:18.786 --> 07:23.094
feel never enters their
calculus, except to manipulate.

07:23.138 --> 07:25.053
"When a Father Leaves."

07:25.096 --> 07:27.447
Ever come across this
in your classes?

07:27.490 --> 07:29.361
- Not as required reading.
More mass market

07:29.405 --> 07:32.539
pop psychology.
- [sighs]

07:32.582 --> 07:34.802
Mrs. Romano,
this is Agent LaCroix.

07:34.845 --> 07:38.545
This is Connie's mom.
- Come in, Mrs. Romano.

07:38.588 --> 07:40.851
- I think somebody
made a mistake.

07:40.895 --> 07:44.072
My daughter's not a bad person.
- Please take a seat.

07:44.115 --> 07:47.423
If anybody made a mistake,
we'll find out.

07:49.730 --> 07:53.603
This is your first time in yourdaughter's apartment, isn't it?

07:53.647 --> 07:56.258
- Well, between her work
and her studies,

07:56.301 --> 07:58.347
Connie doesn't really
have time to--

07:58.390 --> 08:01.481
- To take careof her own mother?

08:01.524 --> 08:03.178
When was the last timeyou saw her?

08:03.221 --> 08:05.920
- Two months ago.
I asked her for help

08:05.963 --> 08:07.922
with my bills,
she turned me down.

08:07.965 --> 08:09.793
- Where would she go
if she was in trouble?

08:09.837 --> 08:12.535
- I-I don't really know
who's in her life these days.

08:12.579 --> 08:15.625
- What about her father?
- [laughs]

08:15.669 --> 08:17.845
We haven't seen Mateo
in 20 years.

08:17.888 --> 08:21.501
Connie was eight when he left.
I raised her myself.

08:21.544 --> 08:24.068
- You've done a good job.

08:24.112 --> 08:28.682
Well, except for that timein Texas.

08:28.725 --> 08:32.512
[tense music]

08:32.555 --> 08:36.472
- Yeah, that was my mistake.
I sent her to El Paso

08:36.516 --> 08:38.169
to stay with my sister
and her husband.

08:38.213 --> 08:40.345
They have three daughters, and
I thought it'd be good for her.

08:40.389 --> 08:43.044
- Instead, she hit it off
with her cousin Ernesto.

08:43.087 --> 08:46.526
We've been trying to find him.
- Nobody knows where he is.

08:46.569 --> 08:48.571
- Just pulled this
out of the laundry hamper.

08:48.615 --> 08:52.357
Looks like someone tried
to get a wine stain out.

08:52.401 --> 08:54.751
No luck on the stain, but
might fit the security guard

08:54.795 --> 08:57.972
who came up to Dr. Pierce.

08:58.015 --> 09:00.278
- Mrs. Matos, we were hoping
you could give us some news

09:00.322 --> 09:02.280
about your daughter.
The security company said

09:02.324 --> 09:03.586
she hasn't been to work
in three days.

09:03.630 --> 09:05.370
[door creaks]

09:05.414 --> 09:08.069
- Amber was supposed to pick up
Zoe from my house on Monday.

09:08.112 --> 09:12.116
She never showed, never called.
School starts in a week.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.075
She wants to know
where Mommy is.

09:14.118 --> 09:16.730
If you don't know,
why are you here?

09:16.773 --> 09:19.776
- Your daughter's been
implicated in a murder,

09:19.820 --> 09:22.387
along with this woman,
Connie Romano.

09:22.431 --> 09:24.172
- That's not possible.
- Her car was at the

09:24.215 --> 09:26.087
crime scene.
She's been identified

09:26.130 --> 09:28.219
as the person who harassed
the victim's fiancé.

09:28.263 --> 09:29.612
- It's just not possible.

09:29.656 --> 09:31.745
Amber tries to be
a good mother.

09:31.788 --> 09:34.138
She stayed in school,
she got a good job.

09:34.182 --> 09:37.054
- We understand it's shocking.
That's why we need to find her.

09:37.098 --> 09:39.666
Do you think she'd reach out
to Zoe's father?

09:39.709 --> 09:41.624
- No.
He was deported back to

09:41.668 --> 09:43.583
Guatemala three years ago.

09:43.626 --> 09:46.107
- How about friends
or relatives?

09:46.150 --> 09:47.717
- All our family
is in Puerto Rico.

09:47.761 --> 09:51.199
And friends,
there's just that one.

09:54.768 --> 09:56.639
- You've met Connie.

09:56.683 --> 10:00.382
- Never met, but heard plenty.
Connie this, Connie that.

10:00.425 --> 10:02.123
Every free moment,
off she went.

10:02.166 --> 10:05.735
- Leaving you to care for Zoe.
- Amber used to take Zoe along

10:05.779 --> 10:08.433
everywhere they went.
But more and more, it was,

10:08.477 --> 10:11.828
"Mama, can you babysit?"
- What do you think changed?

10:11.872 --> 10:14.135
Boyfriends, maybe?

10:14.178 --> 10:16.267
- I never heard Amber
talk about that.

10:19.880 --> 10:21.925
- Would you mind if we spoke
to Zoe about her outings

10:21.969 --> 10:25.450
with Amber and Connie?

10:25.494 --> 10:28.584
- If it helps you
find my Amber.

10:28.628 --> 10:30.673
Please.

10:30.717 --> 10:33.676
[hair dryer running]

10:33.720 --> 10:35.765
Hi, baby, they wanna
talk to you.

10:35.809 --> 10:38.376
- Hey, Zoe.
I'm Jess.

10:38.420 --> 10:41.162
Do you mind if we talk
for a minute?

10:48.735 --> 10:52.782
That's a nice house.
- It's a school, in the trees.

10:52.826 --> 10:57.221
- Oh, I see.
That's a duck pond?

10:59.223 --> 11:02.923
Very pretty.
- You can have it if you like.

11:02.966 --> 11:09.190
- Thank you.
I love it, thanks.

11:09.233 --> 11:10.931
I'd like to talk to you

11:10.974 --> 11:13.716
about your mommy's friend
Connie.

11:13.760 --> 11:17.546
What was your favorite place
you went together?

11:17.589 --> 11:19.330
- Getting ice cream
and cookie dough bowls

11:19.374 --> 11:22.551
after going to the doctor's.
- To the doctor's?

11:22.594 --> 11:24.596
Were you sick?
- No.

11:24.640 --> 11:28.731
She was a feelings doctor.
- A feelings doctor?

11:30.820 --> 11:32.300
Let's see here.

11:34.432 --> 11:37.914
Is that her?
- Dr. Melissa!

11:37.958 --> 11:40.787
- So you and Mommy and Connie
went to Dr. Melissa

11:40.830 --> 11:44.138
to talk about your feelings?
- Only Mommy.

11:44.181 --> 11:47.010
We'd see Miss Connie after,
at the ice cream store.

11:47.054 --> 11:50.753
- And did you meet any other
of Connie's friends?

11:50.797 --> 11:53.800
Maybe a boy?
- There was Mommy's friend,

11:53.843 --> 11:55.932
the boy with the eye
on his neck.

11:55.976 --> 11:58.587
- The boy with the eye
on his neck?

11:58.630 --> 12:01.895
Can you draw that for me?

12:01.938 --> 12:04.767
[dramatic music]

12:04.811 --> 12:07.378
[plastic crinkling]

12:07.422 --> 12:09.641
- Get the nice and easy.
Dark mocha.

12:09.685 --> 12:10.947
Oh, ice.

12:10.991 --> 12:12.253
Don't forget the ice.
Machine's broken.

12:12.296 --> 12:13.689
- Hey, did you talk
to your guy in Sinaloa?

12:13.733 --> 12:15.082
The plane's on its way
from Juarez?

12:15.125 --> 12:17.432
- It's in the air as we speak.
- And you told them

12:17.475 --> 12:21.001
how I took her out, right?
- You didn't take her out.

12:21.044 --> 12:23.830
I did.

12:23.873 --> 12:25.396
Come on.

12:27.747 --> 12:28.791
- [exhales]

12:28.835 --> 12:30.271
[door creaks open and closes]

12:30.314 --> 12:32.752
Otra vez hablando del cártel.

12:32.795 --> 12:34.971
- You can speak English,
Marshall Mathers has left

12:35.015 --> 12:37.104
the building.
- What happens when he finds

12:37.147 --> 12:39.802
out the Cartel isn't in the
market for wannabe assassins

12:39.846 --> 12:43.980
from South Jersey?
- Don't worry about it.

12:44.024 --> 12:47.462
- What is this for?
- You never know.

12:47.505 --> 12:48.768
Be prepared.

12:50.987 --> 12:54.295
- What, do you think
that we can trust him?

12:54.338 --> 12:57.428
- I know how we can find out.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.387
- [sighs deeply]

13:05.697 --> 13:07.830
- The guy with the neck tattoo
might have been a client

13:07.874 --> 13:09.005
of Melissa's.
- With this tattoo,

13:09.049 --> 13:10.528
what he needs
is a plastic surgeon.

13:10.572 --> 13:13.053
- Connie sent Amber and her
daughter on recon missions

13:13.096 --> 13:16.056
to Melissa's office, maybe
to get a fix on her schedule.

13:16.099 --> 13:17.927
- Or maybe just for the thrill
of having the upper hand

13:17.971 --> 13:21.975
in a game Melissa didn't
know she was playing.

13:22.018 --> 13:24.978
[quiet tense music]

13:25.021 --> 13:26.718
♪

13:26.762 --> 13:28.155
- This doesn't look good.

13:30.331 --> 13:32.463
- Oh, man.

13:32.507 --> 13:34.509
- The party never stops
with Connie.

13:36.903 --> 13:39.427
- I don't know what
she's got against fish.

13:39.470 --> 13:41.385
- She's just mean.

13:41.429 --> 13:44.432
- They targeted patient files
H through O.

13:44.475 --> 13:47.957
- Tattoo boy probably stole his
file so he couldn't be traced.

13:48.001 --> 13:49.916
- Check Melissa's patient
billing accounts against

13:49.959 --> 13:54.224
the files in the drawer,
see which ones are missing.

13:54.268 --> 13:57.662
- Somebody peed all over
this desk.

13:57.706 --> 14:01.492
- I'm guessing Connie
marked her turf?

14:01.536 --> 14:03.843
- Amber's car was just found
abandoned five miles

14:03.886 --> 14:06.193
from the murder scene.
- Connie's running the show,

14:06.236 --> 14:09.544
Amber's probably with her.
- Along with Tattoo Boy.

14:09.587 --> 14:11.328
On a road trip to sunny Mexico.

14:11.372 --> 14:14.984
- Connie's got impulsive
cruelty, disinhibition.

14:15.028 --> 14:16.943
All the markers
of a true psychopath.

14:16.986 --> 14:21.469
If I was on the run with her,
I'd fear for my own life.

14:24.037 --> 14:26.387
- Uh, Jared isn't here.
You can't just come in.

14:26.430 --> 14:28.389
- Read the warrant.
Your son has been identified

14:28.432 --> 14:31.479
as a suspect in the murder
of Dr. Melissa Alden.

14:31.522 --> 14:33.916
- But Jared loved Melissa.
He had seen her--

14:33.960 --> 14:35.483
- We know his story,
Mrs. Locke.

14:35.526 --> 14:37.311
We spoke to his
probation officer.

14:37.354 --> 14:39.095
- Your lawyers kept Jared
out of juvie hall for burglary

14:39.139 --> 14:42.359
last year on the condition
of regular psych visits.

14:42.403 --> 14:44.840
- And reports of improvement,
which Dr. Alden refused

14:44.884 --> 14:47.234
to write.

14:47.277 --> 14:49.410
Jared felt betrayed by her,
isn't that correct?

14:49.453 --> 14:52.021
- Jared had a momentary
lapse in judgment.

14:52.065 --> 14:53.588
- Your son had another
lapse in judgment--

14:53.631 --> 14:57.200
this time, it cost
Dr. Alden her life.

14:57.244 --> 14:59.246
- [scoffs]

14:59.289 --> 15:02.162
Welcome to Jared's
House of Narco-Horror.

15:02.205 --> 15:04.381
Check out this playlist.

15:04.425 --> 15:07.689
[song in Spanish playing]

15:07.732 --> 15:11.649
♪

15:11.693 --> 15:14.261
A love song to a drug dealer.

15:14.304 --> 15:16.480
- We got scales, baggies,
and a pipe.

15:16.524 --> 15:20.049
No weed, but this closet
reeks of intent.

15:20.093 --> 15:22.269
- That's just for
medicinal purposes.

15:22.312 --> 15:24.401
- Yeah?
And what does this cure?

15:24.445 --> 15:28.492
Got cut PVC pipe, cotton
wadding, duct tape, a drill.

15:28.536 --> 15:29.841
[drill whirs]

15:29.885 --> 15:31.452
Everything you need
to make a silencer.

15:31.495 --> 15:34.194
- Stop talking about our son
like he's a degenerate killer.

15:34.237 --> 15:38.372
He's just a scared kid.
- You heard it in his voice.

15:38.415 --> 15:41.418
You've spoken to him,
haven't you?

15:41.462 --> 15:43.551
- We've been in contact.

15:43.594 --> 15:45.379
We text him on his
burner phone, he calls it,

15:45.422 --> 15:50.297
and then, uh, he gets
in touch with us when he can.

15:50.340 --> 15:51.994
- I don't have much time.

15:52.038 --> 15:53.778
- Yeah, we're getting
you home, kiddo.

15:53.822 --> 15:55.606
But you're gonna have
to trust us.

15:55.650 --> 15:58.783
- Jared, this is Agent Jess
LaCroix of the FBI.

15:58.827 --> 16:00.524
I promised your parents
I'd do everything I could

16:00.568 --> 16:02.004
to get you home safely.

16:02.048 --> 16:04.050
Do you hear me?
- Uh-huh.

16:04.093 --> 16:05.399
- Good.

16:05.442 --> 16:07.357
You're with Connie and Amber,
is that correct?

16:07.401 --> 16:08.968
- Yeah, they're around.

16:09.011 --> 16:10.099
- You're probably worried
about what'll happen to you

16:10.143 --> 16:11.840
if you turn yourself in.

16:11.883 --> 16:13.624
I give you my word you'll
be treated with more leniency

16:13.668 --> 16:15.583
than Connie and Amber.

16:15.626 --> 16:18.499
- They're not the only ones
that--that I'm dealing with.

16:18.542 --> 16:19.935
You know?
- If you're talking about the

16:19.979 --> 16:22.155
Sinaloa Cartel, we're ahead
of that situation.

16:22.198 --> 16:25.245
You'll be protected.
- If I snitch on Connie,

16:25.288 --> 16:27.987
I'm done.
There's nowhere to hide.

16:28.030 --> 16:29.205
- What are you doing, man?

16:29.249 --> 16:32.774
A true narco does
what he needs to survive.

16:32.817 --> 16:35.864
He certainly wouldn't let a
couple of half-cocked females

16:35.907 --> 16:37.387
call the shots on his life.

16:37.431 --> 16:38.736
- What size bag of ice
you want?

16:38.780 --> 16:41.130
- Biggest one you got,
our machine's broken.

16:41.174 --> 16:42.610
- Jared?

16:42.653 --> 16:44.960
Take the offer
and beat the rap.

16:45.004 --> 16:48.311
We can be anywhere
within five hours.

16:48.355 --> 16:51.314
- Meet me outside Cacciatori
Pizza in Raleigh.

16:54.665 --> 16:56.189
- Couldn't get an exact
location.

16:56.232 --> 16:58.147
North Carolina,
within 100 miles of Raleigh.

16:58.191 --> 17:03.370
- I got a lock on a Cacciatori
in East Raleigh off the 440.

17:03.413 --> 17:05.546
- Do you like it?
- I'll put it right over here.

17:05.589 --> 17:07.200
Look, I was gonna get--

17:07.243 --> 17:08.418
- Hey, yo, uh,
I'm getting out of here.

17:08.462 --> 17:10.029
I'm gonna grab
some cold beers.

17:10.072 --> 17:12.248
- Make sure you put more
pictures up--

17:12.292 --> 17:15.164
- What about some real relief?

17:15.208 --> 17:18.298
Like--like, maybe a shower?
[laughs]

17:20.300 --> 17:22.954
- I'm gonna get
the beers first.

17:22.998 --> 17:26.219
- You heard what the girl said.
- Mm.

17:26.262 --> 17:30.788
- It's your lucky day.
So I'll get the beers.

17:30.832 --> 17:31.833
[laughs softly]

17:34.401 --> 17:37.360
[tense music]

17:37.404 --> 17:39.493
♪

17:39.536 --> 17:41.973
[both laugh quietly]

17:42.017 --> 17:44.193
[water running]

17:46.500 --> 17:49.546
- [sighs]

17:49.590 --> 17:51.896
- Do you guys mind if I join?

17:55.378 --> 17:56.858
You called your mommy?

17:59.643 --> 18:02.603
- [gasps]
- [grunting]

18:08.043 --> 18:13.831
- Jared's overdue by an hour.
- "You know what a 'hassa' is?"

18:13.875 --> 18:16.356
It's "Scarface" for a pig
that doesn't fly straight.

18:16.399 --> 18:19.533
Jared lied to us.
- He was ready to deal.

18:19.576 --> 18:21.535
Something's up.

18:21.578 --> 18:23.493
On the call,
he was buying a bag of ice.

18:23.537 --> 18:25.495
He said,
"Our machine is broken."

18:25.539 --> 18:27.497
Probably at a motel.

18:27.541 --> 18:29.673
- Like, for example,
across the street.

18:29.717 --> 18:32.894
- Let's go bust some
doors down.

18:32.937 --> 18:35.026
- Front desk ID'd Connie
from the photos.

18:35.070 --> 18:37.159
Room 230.

18:37.203 --> 18:40.162
[suspenseful music]

18:40.206 --> 18:47.213
♪

18:57.266 --> 18:59.529
[water running]

18:59.573 --> 19:01.749
- We got a body.

19:14.327 --> 19:17.678
- His parents' number.
Our boy got made.

19:23.423 --> 19:26.426
- Amber seduces,
Connie executes.

19:26.469 --> 19:28.863
Quite a tag team.
- The license plate that was on

19:28.906 --> 19:31.474
Jared's car was just
found in a parking lot

19:31.518 --> 19:33.389
in Emporia, Virginia.

19:33.433 --> 19:35.435
They must've switched
plates on the car.

19:35.478 --> 19:37.698
- I've been diving into the
sisterhood of the traveling

19:37.741 --> 19:40.788
body count.
Amber's page is all BFF photos

19:40.831 --> 19:43.225
of her and Connie.
Swing over to Connie's page,

19:43.269 --> 19:46.185
and any photo of the two of
them was tagged by Amber first.

19:46.228 --> 19:48.099
That's a one-way girl crush.

19:48.143 --> 19:50.232
- So Amber's in love
with Connie?

19:50.276 --> 19:53.453
- Or just wants to be Connie.
- Which no doubt feeds into

19:53.496 --> 19:57.500
Connie's narcissism.
What are those posts?

19:57.544 --> 19:59.415
Woodmont Preparatory School.

19:59.459 --> 20:02.723
- Some school Amber
looked up for her kid.

20:02.766 --> 20:06.640
[tense music]

20:06.683 --> 20:11.122
- Barnes, check this out.
The school in the trees.

20:11.166 --> 20:13.255
- Mm.

20:13.299 --> 20:16.693
And there's Zoe, headed to
Woodmont with Mom and Connie.

20:16.737 --> 20:18.652
- I don't know how Amber
would afford it on a

20:18.695 --> 20:21.742
security guard's salary.

20:21.785 --> 20:24.135
- Robbie Pierce, the plastic
surgeon, he could afford it.

20:26.399 --> 20:31.317
Maybe Connie promised to foot
the bill if Amber helped her

20:31.360 --> 20:34.363
get back with Robbie.
- By killing Melissa.

20:34.407 --> 20:36.539
- And lucky for Amber,
Connie's not the only one

20:36.583 --> 20:39.499
who can make dreams come true.

20:39.542 --> 20:41.370
[door creaks]

20:41.414 --> 20:44.373
[rock music playing]

20:44.417 --> 20:48.769
♪

20:48.812 --> 20:50.118
- [scoffs]

20:50.161 --> 20:53.121
No, you're bad luck to me.

20:53.164 --> 20:57.865
Eight years of bad luck.
For a stunt you talked me into.

20:57.908 --> 21:01.085
Gunrunning--the hell
were you thinking about?

21:01.129 --> 21:03.827
- Money.
For me, for you.

21:09.703 --> 21:13.054
Please, Ernesto--
- Oh, no, don't call me that.

21:13.097 --> 21:16.013
I'm Simon Reyes now.
I worked hard to leave Texas

21:16.057 --> 21:18.842
and those people behind.
- The FBI's looking for me.

21:18.886 --> 21:22.063
- Oh, you'll weasel your way
out, that's what you do.

21:22.106 --> 21:26.241
- Look, I didn't kill anybody.
He was my ex, the surgeon.

21:26.285 --> 21:29.200
- Why are you telling me this?

21:29.244 --> 21:31.855
- That's my friend over there,and we're headed to Mexico.

21:31.899 --> 21:34.380
But we need somewhere safe
to get to.

21:34.423 --> 21:35.903
[cell phone buzzes]

21:35.946 --> 21:37.383
You can help us.
- [laughs softly]

21:37.426 --> 21:39.689
- Maybe you can get the word
out to someone in Sinaloa.

21:39.733 --> 21:41.822
Yeah?
- You crazy?

21:41.865 --> 21:45.260
That's not me.
I knew one guy down there.

21:45.304 --> 21:49.569
- I have money.Little over a grand.

21:49.612 --> 21:50.961
Come on.

21:54.095 --> 21:55.879
- There's a guy
in Atlanta I met.

21:55.923 --> 21:58.099
Used to run drugs
for the Cartel.

21:58.142 --> 22:01.624
I gotta call him first.
If he's cool, I'll call you.

22:01.668 --> 22:06.455
But I'm taking this money.
Regardless.

22:06.499 --> 22:08.109
Now get out of my bar.

22:10.024 --> 22:12.766
- [breathes deeply]

22:12.809 --> 22:15.812
He's gonna help us.
- Oh, okay.

22:15.856 --> 22:18.293
- What were you looking at?

22:18.337 --> 22:20.730
- Oh, uh, just shots of Zoe.
It's, you know, it's hard.

22:20.774 --> 22:22.993
I miss my daughter.
- But once we cross the border,

22:23.037 --> 22:24.865
it'll be okay.
- I know, I just, um--

22:24.908 --> 22:26.997
- Just what?

22:27.041 --> 22:29.086
- I'm--I'm gonna use
the bathroom.

22:29.130 --> 22:30.610
Do you need to go?
No?

22:30.653 --> 22:32.742
Okay, just give me a second.

22:32.786 --> 22:34.396
[door opens]

22:39.532 --> 22:41.838
[phone ringing]

22:44.275 --> 22:46.756
[keys clacking]

22:46.800 --> 22:49.846
- Woodmont Prep, financial aid.
This is Kelly.

22:49.890 --> 22:52.283
- Yes, hi, um, I got a message
regarding my daughter,

22:52.327 --> 22:53.546
Zoe Matos.

22:53.589 --> 22:55.635
- Oh, yes.
Thank you for calling back.

22:55.678 --> 22:57.288
We have good news.

22:57.332 --> 22:59.421
One of our new students with a
full scholarship for next year

22:59.465 --> 23:02.511
had to withdraw because her
family is leaving the country.

23:02.555 --> 23:04.818
That leaves a spot open
for another applicant.

23:04.861 --> 23:08.169
- Oh, my God.
Are you serious?

23:08.212 --> 23:09.910
- Yes.
I see you were looking

23:09.953 --> 23:12.216
for a spot for next spring.
This would be for the fall.

23:12.260 --> 23:13.566
Would that be a problem?

23:13.609 --> 23:15.524
- No, no, it's--
that's not a problem.

23:15.568 --> 23:16.917
We can definitely
make that work.

23:16.960 --> 23:18.048
It's not a problem at all.

23:18.092 --> 23:19.354
- Awesome.

23:19.398 --> 23:22.662
We'll get Zoe in
for a face-to-face tomorrow?

23:22.705 --> 23:23.967
- Um...

23:26.056 --> 23:27.362
Uh, can my mom bring her in?

23:27.406 --> 23:28.668
- Afraid not.

23:28.711 --> 23:30.060
We need parent signatures.

23:30.104 --> 23:32.367
- Oh, I'm out of town
for work right now,

23:32.411 --> 23:36.066
so I can't really make that.
- I can talk to my director.

23:36.110 --> 23:38.417
Uh, maybe if you designate
your mother as guardian,

23:38.460 --> 23:41.637
we can send a form.
Hang on a few minutes.

23:41.681 --> 23:43.160
[knocking on door]

23:43.204 --> 23:45.946
- Amber, we gotta go.
- I-I have to--

23:45.989 --> 23:48.557
I have to go right now.
Um, please, please, please

23:48.601 --> 23:50.298
hold this spot for my daughter,
so maybe she--

23:50.341 --> 23:52.169
she's really a smart kid.
She really needs this

23:52.213 --> 23:56.260
right now, so let me--
let me just call you back.

23:56.304 --> 23:58.393
- All right, the signal's
just outside Charlotte,

23:58.437 --> 24:00.961
near Old Monroe Road
in Stallings.

24:01.004 --> 24:02.963
It's on the move,
heading south.

24:03.006 --> 24:06.619
- Get all local units on it.

24:06.662 --> 24:09.186
[helicopter rotors buzzing]

24:09.230 --> 24:12.189
[suspenseful music]

24:12.233 --> 24:18.544
♪

24:19.936 --> 24:23.505
- Just come this way, agents.

24:23.549 --> 24:26.334
We found it abandoned.
There's a phone left

24:26.377 --> 24:28.249
on the passenger seat.
- It's the same make

24:28.292 --> 24:32.166
of Jared's car.
Different license plate.

24:32.209 --> 24:35.430
[crickets chirping]

24:35.474 --> 24:37.171
- Found the phone.
Looks like Amber's.

24:37.214 --> 24:39.565
- Connie left it to send
us another message.

24:39.608 --> 24:41.262
- Hope it's not
bad news for Amber.

24:41.305 --> 24:43.438
- [grunts]

24:43.482 --> 24:45.527
A prescription for Connie.

24:45.571 --> 24:49.444
Check out the
prescribing doctor.

24:49.488 --> 24:52.229
- You wrote the prescription
for Connie three days before

24:52.273 --> 24:55.537
Melissa died.
So much for your clean break.

24:55.581 --> 24:57.104
- [scoffs]

24:57.147 --> 24:59.889
Okay, before I was Connie's
boyfriend, I was her doctor.

24:59.933 --> 25:02.370
After we broke up, I couldn't
abandon her medically,

25:02.413 --> 25:04.198
so, whatever, yes.
I wrote the prescription.

25:04.241 --> 25:06.766
- Then why not tell us?
I mean, beside the optics of,

25:06.809 --> 25:09.072
uh, sleeping with your ex
right before she executed

25:09.116 --> 25:10.857
your fiancée.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa--

25:10.900 --> 25:13.555
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, yourself.
You double down on your lie

25:13.599 --> 25:15.165
and you make us check
the video surveillance

25:15.209 --> 25:17.080
at your apartment building,
the only way you'll see Hawaii

25:17.124 --> 25:19.561
is by postcard.

25:19.605 --> 25:23.086
[soft tense music]

25:23.130 --> 25:25.828
- It was only the once.

25:25.872 --> 25:28.309
After Connie found out
about Hawaii,

25:28.352 --> 25:31.791
she came by to drop off
a going-away present.

25:31.834 --> 25:35.446
I felt sorry for her.
- Pity sex, that's your excuse?

25:35.490 --> 25:37.013
- This doesn't change
anything, though.

25:37.057 --> 25:38.754
I was still in love
with Melissa.

25:38.798 --> 25:42.584
I--I was still leaving.
I told Connie as much.

25:42.628 --> 25:46.632
- You gave Connie hope.
You set her off.

25:46.675 --> 25:48.024
Now you're gonna
make it right.

25:53.987 --> 25:55.423
- Thanks.

25:55.466 --> 25:59.296
Connie.
Okay.

25:59.340 --> 26:03.300
You're not gonna talk to me?
Connie?

26:03.344 --> 26:06.303
- You're an idiot, Amber.
A scholarship from the sky?

26:06.347 --> 26:08.349
Do you know what you almost
gave up with that call?

26:08.392 --> 26:11.047
They could've traced it,
and seen our car.

26:11.091 --> 26:14.529
You're so lucky to be with me.
- Mm-hmm.

26:16.531 --> 26:18.098
- [breathes shakily]
We're low.

26:18.141 --> 26:19.926
- What do you mean we're low?
You said we had enough.

26:19.969 --> 26:22.145
- Well, 1,000 went to Ernesto,
and another grand went to his

26:22.189 --> 26:24.147
guy in Atlanta,
so we need cash.

26:24.191 --> 26:27.934
- [sighs]
- I saw a motel nearby.

26:27.977 --> 26:30.676
I'll negotiate a price
to cover the room, okay?

26:30.719 --> 26:33.069
- Okay, I'll wait here
with our stuff.

26:33.113 --> 26:34.070
- All right,
and don't worry about

26:34.114 --> 26:36.377
any rough stuff, all right?

26:36.420 --> 26:38.858
I still have the gun,
so I'll be close by, okay?

26:38.901 --> 26:41.687
Don't worry.
- Are you asking me to--

26:41.730 --> 26:44.298
- I'm not asking, Amber.
It's your fault

26:44.341 --> 26:46.300
that we had to give up the car.
Now it's your turn

26:46.343 --> 26:48.215
to make up for it.

26:51.392 --> 26:54.917
- Please don't make me do this.
- Suck it up, Amber.

26:54.961 --> 26:56.615
Let's go.

26:58.529 --> 27:01.054
[dramatic music]

27:01.097 --> 27:03.883
[upbeat music playing
in earbuds]

27:03.926 --> 27:06.059
[man grunting]

27:06.102 --> 27:08.627
[cell phone chimes]

27:11.455 --> 27:14.415
[tense music]

27:14.458 --> 27:17.548
♪

27:17.592 --> 27:19.681
- The Connie I know
is far from perfect.

27:19.725 --> 27:21.988
But I just don't believe
she killed Melissa.

27:22.031 --> 27:25.034
She's not evil.
Now, Melissa's patient,

27:25.078 --> 27:27.341
Jared Locke, he was
the one with the grudge.

27:27.384 --> 27:29.865
I-I think that Connie
tried to stop him.

27:29.909 --> 27:31.562
And now she's scared.

27:31.606 --> 27:35.262
- Robbie, if you could talk
to Connie, what would you say?

27:35.305 --> 27:37.307
- Stop running, Connie.

27:37.351 --> 27:39.309
I think you know
how I feel about you.

27:39.353 --> 27:41.355
I will stand by you,
I will get you a lawyer.

27:41.398 --> 27:45.664
Just--just reach out,
any way you can.

27:49.755 --> 27:52.714
- It came in ten minutes ago
to Robbie Pierce's Instagram.

27:52.758 --> 27:56.196
- Hey, you don't know me,
but I know your girl Connie.

27:56.239 --> 27:58.154
I saw you on TV.

27:58.198 --> 27:59.808
I think I can help you
get in touch with Connie,

27:59.852 --> 28:02.158
but it'll take
some effort from you.

28:02.202 --> 28:06.772
Paid effort.
Call me back.

28:06.815 --> 28:08.687
- You heard him.
Hit him back.

28:08.730 --> 28:10.732
Set a meeting.
And drill his phone.

28:10.776 --> 28:13.692
I want every message
he sent in the last week.

28:13.735 --> 28:16.085
[suspenseful music]

28:16.129 --> 28:18.740
- [grunts]

28:18.784 --> 28:21.221
Can I help you?
- You tell us.

28:21.264 --> 28:24.093
- Dr. Pierce couldn't make it.
- Son of a bitch.

28:24.137 --> 28:26.008
- We're not interested
in putting you back in jail,

28:26.052 --> 28:28.924
Mr. Cruz.
We want your cousin Connie.

28:28.968 --> 28:30.752
- I don't know where she is--
- We've got you texting

28:30.796 --> 28:33.102
back and forth with her,
on and on about getting a known

28:33.146 --> 28:35.888
fugitive across the border.
- Bitch.

28:38.760 --> 28:41.284
She's all about
going to Mexico.

28:41.328 --> 28:42.808
I told her I'll hook her up
with a dude

28:42.851 --> 28:45.680
who could make it happen.
- Cartel associate.

28:45.724 --> 28:47.769
- Yeah, who's been dead
five years.

28:47.813 --> 28:50.946
I was playing her, man.
The cartel stuff?

28:50.990 --> 28:54.820
I told Connie that when
she was 16, to impress her.

28:54.863 --> 28:57.953
I got no connects
with the cartels.

28:57.997 --> 29:00.956
[soft dramatic music]

29:01.000 --> 29:03.829
- You do now.

29:03.872 --> 29:06.701
[thunder crackling]

29:06.745 --> 29:13.447
♪

29:19.192 --> 29:22.412
- Hey.
Esta la chica.

29:31.900 --> 29:34.250
- She's going.
Stay there.

29:36.949 --> 29:39.778
[both panting]

29:41.692 --> 29:43.694
[all grunt]

29:46.132 --> 29:49.657
- [panting]

29:49.700 --> 29:53.835
- Nine mil.
Looks like the murder weapon.

29:53.879 --> 29:56.403
- You're just making things
worse for yourself, Amber.

29:56.446 --> 29:58.535
Why don't you tell us
where Connie is?

29:58.579 --> 30:02.322
[indistinct radio chatter]

30:02.365 --> 30:04.715
- Chesterfield Motel.

30:06.587 --> 30:10.069
- Front room is clear.

30:10.112 --> 30:12.723
[muffled sobbing]

30:18.512 --> 30:21.254
- Oh, thank God!
I really thought she was gonna

30:21.297 --> 30:25.084
kill me this time.
- Who?

30:25.127 --> 30:27.521
Amber.
You know, she killed Melissa.

30:27.564 --> 30:29.871
I saw her.
I tried to save her,

30:29.915 --> 30:31.873
I really did, but then Jared,
he had a gun.

30:31.917 --> 30:34.267
- Okay, take it easy.
Take it easy.

30:34.310 --> 30:35.877
- You know, they forced me
into the car, they said

30:35.921 --> 30:38.140
that I had to take
them to Mexico.

30:38.184 --> 30:39.968
After I sent the video,
I just prayed

30:40.012 --> 30:43.058
that someone would find me.
- What video is this?

30:43.102 --> 30:46.932
- The one I posted to Facebook.
Did it not go through?

30:56.550 --> 30:59.335
- My name is Connie Romano.

30:59.379 --> 31:02.773
I'm being held against
my will by Amber Matos.

31:02.817 --> 31:06.125
She's in the next room,
hooking up with some guy.

31:06.168 --> 31:08.736
I'm in a motel
somewhere in Georgia.

31:08.779 --> 31:11.565
Please, please help me.

31:11.608 --> 31:16.265
I did not kill Melissa Alden.
Amber Matos did.

31:16.309 --> 31:19.225
And she killed Jared Locke.
And if somebody doesn't

31:19.268 --> 31:22.445
find me soon,
I'm gonna be next.

31:22.489 --> 31:24.970
Please contact the police
and tell them that--

31:25.013 --> 31:26.014
[gasps]

31:27.929 --> 31:30.105
- You buy it?
She could've tied herself up.

31:30.149 --> 31:32.238
- Her plastic ties
seemed a bit loose.

31:32.281 --> 31:35.023
She could've slipped out
whenever she wanted to.

31:35.067 --> 31:38.722
[foreboding music]

31:38.766 --> 31:41.073
- I did not kill
Melissa Alden.

31:41.116 --> 31:44.903
Amber Matos did.
And she killed Jared Locke.

31:44.946 --> 31:47.079
And if somebody doesn't
find me soon,

31:47.122 --> 31:49.559
I'm gonna be next.
Please contact the--

31:49.603 --> 31:52.171
- Ms. Matos, I advise you
not to say anything.

31:52.214 --> 31:53.999
- Not even to deny
what her friend said?

31:54.042 --> 31:55.696
- It's obviously
a self-serving statement

31:55.739 --> 31:58.220
with no probative value.
- I wouldn't be so sure.

31:58.264 --> 32:01.006
There's no evidence to suggest
that Connie was anything

32:01.049 --> 32:05.010
but an interested bystander
in the murder of Melissa Alden.

32:05.053 --> 32:07.490
Amber had the murder weapon
on her when we arrested her.

32:07.534 --> 32:09.884
- There's evidence Amber had
a prior relationship with the

32:09.928 --> 32:12.321
shooter Jared Locke.
And evidence she was in the

32:12.365 --> 32:14.933
shower with Jared
when he was killed.

32:14.976 --> 32:18.066
A jury will likely find
her guilty of both murders,

32:18.110 --> 32:21.940
while odds are Connie
will walk.

32:21.983 --> 32:23.767
- Is that the backup plan,
Amber?

32:23.811 --> 32:25.421
We find you at the park,
and you take the blame

32:25.465 --> 32:27.554
for everything to save Connie?

32:31.036 --> 32:33.473
- I need to talk to my client.

32:33.516 --> 32:37.085
- Let me give you
something to talk about.

32:37.129 --> 32:39.174
[sighs]

32:43.526 --> 32:46.094
I'm sure Connie promised you
that once she got back

32:46.138 --> 32:48.227
with Robbie,
she'd hire the best lawyers.

32:48.270 --> 32:50.969
I'm sure she promised you
she'd use Robbie's money

32:51.012 --> 32:54.015
to get Zoe into Woodmont.
We spoke to Robbie.

32:54.059 --> 32:56.844
It's not gonna happen.

32:56.887 --> 33:00.021
Connie sold you a lie.

33:00.065 --> 33:04.591
[dramatic music]

33:04.634 --> 33:06.332
- There's only one reason
I'm here, and it's the choices

33:06.375 --> 33:10.031
I've made.
- [scoffs]

33:10.075 --> 33:13.513
What about Zoe's choice?
What about her choices?

33:13.556 --> 33:16.690
Huh?
What do you think she'd choose?

33:16.733 --> 33:19.649
To go to a fancy school or to
have her mother to hold her?

33:19.693 --> 33:21.956
Because if you do
what Connie wants,

33:22.000 --> 33:24.915
you'll be out
of her life forever.

33:24.959 --> 33:30.008
♪

33:30.051 --> 33:32.619
- [sniffles]

33:32.662 --> 33:36.971
- I know Conniemakes you feel special.

33:37.015 --> 33:39.321
But she doesn't value you.She uses you.

33:39.365 --> 33:42.542
That's her nature.She used you when she sent you

33:42.585 --> 33:45.240
to talk to Robbie.She used you when she sent you

33:45.284 --> 33:46.894
to the park today.

33:49.114 --> 33:51.725
This right here,your daughter.

33:54.075 --> 33:57.687
This is all that matters.

34:06.696 --> 34:08.655
- It was me,
I did everything.

34:11.875 --> 34:14.226
[sniffles]
It was me.

34:16.271 --> 34:17.881
- Between the video
and Amber's statement,

34:17.925 --> 34:20.232
Connie could hang the jury.
With a half-decent lawyer,

34:20.275 --> 34:22.364
she can cut herself
a pretty sweet deal.

34:22.408 --> 34:24.279
- While Amber does life
for two murders.

34:24.323 --> 34:25.802
It's wrong.
- She thinks she's giving

34:25.846 --> 34:28.153
her child a chance
at a better life.

34:28.196 --> 34:30.024
- Connie's lucky she found
a weak person to even

34:30.068 --> 34:31.721
take the fall.
- Psychopaths don't just prey

34:31.765 --> 34:33.897
on the weak.
Connie gave Amber what every

34:33.941 --> 34:35.899
human being wants--
a connection.

34:35.943 --> 34:38.119
Sense of belonging.
It's very powerful.

34:38.163 --> 34:40.687
Amber probably thinks the day
she met Connie was the second

34:40.730 --> 34:43.298
best day of her life, and
Connie won't let her forget it.

34:43.342 --> 34:46.475
She needs a sycophant
to control, to manipulate.

34:46.519 --> 34:48.216
[cell phone buzzes]

34:48.260 --> 34:51.263
Otherwise her outsized sense
of self would crumble.

34:51.306 --> 34:53.830
- The Monmouth County DA's
office started the extradition

34:53.874 --> 34:55.571
process against
Connie and Amber.

34:55.615 --> 34:57.182
- They're gonna have
a mess on their hands.

34:57.225 --> 34:59.053
- Dig up all you can
on Connie's father,

34:59.097 --> 35:01.186
the one that abandoned her
when she was a kid.

35:03.666 --> 35:06.147
We can't do it.
We can't just kick the can

35:06.191 --> 35:08.062
down the road.

35:08.106 --> 35:12.371
We have to sort this out now.
We have to try.

35:12.414 --> 35:13.894
First, let me say how
relieved we are

35:13.937 --> 35:17.202
we got to you in time.
It must've been hell.

35:17.245 --> 35:20.466
- I'm just glad that
someone finally heard me.

35:20.509 --> 35:23.512
- You have our full support.
Before we go on,

35:23.556 --> 35:25.079
we heard you didn't
want a lawyer.

35:25.123 --> 35:27.777
- I don't need one.
I'm the victim here.

35:27.821 --> 35:29.562
- Well, you're certainly
intelligent enough to know

35:29.605 --> 35:32.652
if you'd need one or not.
So, no lawyer?

35:32.695 --> 35:35.829
- No lawyer.
- Okay.

35:35.872 --> 35:37.831
- After all you've been
through, is there anyone we can

35:37.874 --> 35:39.659
call for you?
A friend?

35:39.702 --> 35:44.229
- I heard what Robbie did,
what he said on my behalf.

35:44.272 --> 35:47.057
I'd like to see him.

35:47.101 --> 35:51.845
- Oh, well, nobody told you?

35:51.888 --> 35:56.110
- Yes, I know it was you
behind the interview.

35:56.154 --> 36:00.723
But I could tell--
what he said, he meant.

36:00.767 --> 36:02.769
- No, no, no, no.
We scripted the whole thing.

36:02.812 --> 36:04.640
Had to force Robbie
to do it, actually.

36:04.684 --> 36:06.468
Truth is, he said he wants
to stay as far away from you

36:06.512 --> 36:09.689
as possible.
- He's just scared.

36:09.732 --> 36:12.213
[laughs]
I'm sure he'll get over it.

36:12.257 --> 36:14.389
- You say that because he had
sex with you right before

36:14.433 --> 36:16.609
Melissa died?
Yeah, he told us

36:16.652 --> 36:21.918
he felt sorry for you.
Pity sex is what he called it.

36:21.962 --> 36:24.094
- Pity sex?
- Mm.

36:24.138 --> 36:27.707
- Yeah.
- Pity sex.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.361
- Maybe we could call
somebody else.

36:29.404 --> 36:32.233
Not your mother, we know
there are complications there,

36:32.277 --> 36:34.975
but maybe your dad.

36:35.018 --> 36:39.197
- I'm sorry, who?
- Your father, Mateo.

36:39.240 --> 36:42.112
Took us a while to find him.
He shortened his last name,

36:42.156 --> 36:44.680
anglicized his first.
He goes by the name...

36:44.724 --> 36:47.074
- Matt Roman.
- Matt Roman.

36:47.117 --> 36:51.209
We had to use his social
to find him.

36:51.252 --> 36:56.083
It's a nice looking family.
His second family.

36:56.126 --> 36:59.391
[quiet dramatic music]

36:59.434 --> 37:02.307
Is that the first time
you've seen his page?

37:02.350 --> 37:05.092
♪

37:05.135 --> 37:07.137
- I never looked for it.

37:07.181 --> 37:08.313
- No, of course, there's...

37:08.356 --> 37:09.966
nothing of interest
to you here.

37:10.010 --> 37:12.752
It's just him and his wife
and his kids--

37:12.795 --> 37:16.495
beautiful kids.
Not one picture of you, though.

37:16.538 --> 37:19.889
Didn't your mother send him
pictures of you growing up?

37:26.069 --> 37:28.071
How old were you
when he abandoned you?

37:30.596 --> 37:33.076
- Eight.
- Eight years old.

37:36.254 --> 37:40.606
So he really knew
who he was leaving.

37:40.649 --> 37:44.479
Were you at home when he left?
You watch him drive away?

37:44.523 --> 37:47.308
- [scoffs]

37:47.352 --> 37:49.223
I stopped caring
a long time ago.

37:49.267 --> 37:52.008
- Yeah, I used to tell
myself the same thing.

37:52.052 --> 37:54.576
My dad's a real bastard too.
[sighs]

37:54.620 --> 37:59.233
You try to kill off
those feelings, but you can't.

37:59.277 --> 38:01.714
It's kinda like when Robbie
tried to go to Hawaii,

38:01.757 --> 38:03.324
and you did everything
you could to stop him.

38:03.368 --> 38:05.544
- I told you.
That was all Amber.

38:05.587 --> 38:07.372
- I wouldn't rely
too much on Amber.

38:07.415 --> 38:09.330
Once she hears no one's paying
for her daughter's school,

38:09.374 --> 38:10.723
she'll wise up.

38:12.986 --> 38:14.683
- We spoke to your father.

38:14.727 --> 38:16.946
Told him his daughter
was in trouble.

38:16.990 --> 38:19.862
He was in a total panic.
What father wouldn't be?

38:19.906 --> 38:21.821
But he thought we were
talking about Sara,

38:21.864 --> 38:24.127
your stepsister
who's away at college.

38:24.171 --> 38:26.304
- And when we told him
it was you in trouble,

38:26.347 --> 38:28.480
he couldn't wait
to get off the phone.

38:31.134 --> 38:34.312
- He told us he had
nothing to do with you.

38:34.355 --> 38:39.404
But you and I both know he had
everything to do with you.

38:39.447 --> 38:40.709
Everything to do
with your pain,

38:40.753 --> 38:42.885
everything to do
with your anger.

38:47.325 --> 38:49.588
I look at this picture...

38:52.242 --> 38:53.766
At this piece of crap father...

38:57.552 --> 39:00.381
And I think to myself I would
do anything I could to wipe

39:00.425 --> 39:04.124
that self-satisfied smile
off his face.

39:04.167 --> 39:06.169
Hmm?

39:06.213 --> 39:09.999
Wouldn't you like to do that?
I would.

39:10.043 --> 39:12.262
It's not fair that he's gonna
go on living his life

39:12.306 --> 39:15.527
without anybody knowing
the chaos he left behind.

39:15.570 --> 39:19.444
You think his wife, his kids
know that he left you

39:19.487 --> 39:21.750
and your mother to struggle?
You think they know that

39:21.794 --> 39:27.147
everything you did was
because he made you do it?

39:27.190 --> 39:29.845
He made you.
- Shut up, shut up,

39:29.889 --> 39:31.891
and get the hell
out of my head.

39:31.934 --> 39:34.284
- It's not me in your head.

39:49.212 --> 39:51.345
It's your father in your head.

39:55.349 --> 39:59.527
Is that whose face you sawwhen you crushed Melissa's?

39:59.571 --> 40:04.184
Come on, Connie.Put the blood on his hands.

40:04.227 --> 40:06.926
Where it belongs.
- [sniffles]

40:21.419 --> 40:23.638
Melissa died quick.

40:25.597 --> 40:29.165
He doesn't deserve
that much mercy.

40:29.209 --> 40:33.561
If it was him instead of her,
I would've taken my time.

40:36.608 --> 40:38.610
You can tell him that
when you talk to him.

40:42.701 --> 40:47.749
I'm his daughter.
I'm his daughter.

40:47.793 --> 40:51.666
And this is what I did.

40:51.710 --> 40:54.974
And he should feel ashamed
for hurting me.

41:08.814 --> 41:12.252
- We got everything on tape.
- Now Jersey can have her.

41:18.563 --> 41:21.000
- Can you send me the number
for that school?

41:21.043 --> 41:23.916
Maybe there's a program Amber's
daughter can qualify for.

41:23.959 --> 41:25.570
She had nothing to do
with any of this.

41:25.613 --> 41:28.355
Maybe she can have
a soft landing.

41:33.447 --> 41:36.058
[brush dabbing on wood]

41:39.235 --> 41:41.542
- Hey, Dad.
- Hi, sweetie.

41:41.586 --> 41:43.718
- I'm, uh, I'm almost
finished with the bat box.

41:43.762 --> 41:47.287
- Looks good.

41:47.330 --> 41:48.723
[wood block scraping]

41:48.767 --> 41:50.899
Hey, did you get the texts
I sent you about that boy?

41:50.943 --> 41:53.423
- Uh-huh.
But I worked it out.

41:53.467 --> 41:56.557
I told Ross I didn't want
to play with him anymore.

41:56.601 --> 41:59.604
And then he apologized.

41:59.647 --> 42:01.649
He said he felt bad
about the hawk.

42:01.693 --> 42:04.086
- Well, that's good.
I thought when you told me

42:04.130 --> 42:07.873
about it, you wanted
my help resolving it.

42:07.916 --> 42:10.440
- No, I was just upset.

42:12.268 --> 42:15.402
But thanks for listening.
- Sure.

42:15.445 --> 42:18.318
[gentle music]

42:18.361 --> 42:20.625
Anytime.

42:20.668 --> 42:22.496
- Hot chocolate helped too.

42:22.540 --> 42:29.503
♪

42:45.998 --> 42:48.957
[dramatic music]

42:49.001 --> 42:56.008
♪

43:06.018 --> 43:06.758
[wolf howls]
